{{Pie chart | thumb =right | caption =Mexico total primary energy consumption by fuel in 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bp.com/content/dam/bp/pdf/energy-economics/statistical-review-2016/bp-statistical-review-of-world-energy-2016-full-report.pdf|title=Statistical Review of World Energy (June 2016)|publisher=}}</ref> | other = | label1 =Coal | value1 =7 | color1 =#313c42 | label2 =Natural Gas | value2 =41 | color2 =#ef8e39 | label3 =Hydro | value3 =4 | color3 =#005CE6 | label4 =Nuclear | value4 =1 | color4 =#de2821 | label5 =Oil | value5 =45 | color5 =#7C6250 | label6 =Others ([[Renewables|Renew.]]) | value6 =2 | color6 =#00CC4B }} '''Energy in Mexico''' describes [[World energy resources and consumption|energy]] and [[Electricity generation|electricity]] production, consumption and import in [[Mexico]]. [[Electricity sector in Mexico]] is the main article of electricity in Mexico.
In 2008, Mexico produced 234 [[TWh]], from which 86 TWh are coming from thermal plant, 39 TWh from hydro-power, 18 TWh from [[coal]], 9,8 TWh from [[nuclear power]], 7 TWh from geothermal power and 0,255 TWh from [[wind power]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.energia.gob.mx/webSener/portal/index.jsp?id=71 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2009-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091219204310/http://www.energia.gob.mx/webSener/portal/index.jsp?id=71 |archive-date=2009-12-19 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> Mexico is among the top [[Oil reserves|oil producers]] and exporters in the world.
