{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=October 2016}} '''Hugh Saddler''' has a degree in science from [[Adelaide University]] and a PhD from [[Cambridge University]]. He is the author of a book on Australian energy policy, ''Energy in Australia'' and over 50 scientific papers, monographs and articles on [[energy technology]] and [[environmental policy]], and is recognised as one of Australia's leading experts in this field.<ref name=hugh>[http://www.enerstrat.com.au/ourstaff.html#hs Energy Strategies staff]</ref>
Hugh Saddler is currently a member of the Experts Group on Emissions Trading, appointed by the [[Australian Greenhouse Office]], of the ABS Environmental Statistics Advisory Group, and of the ACT Environment Advisory Committee. In 1998 he was appointed an Adjunct Professor at Murdoch University. He is a Fellow of the Australian Institute of Energy and a member of the International Association for Energy Economics.<ref name=hugh/>
Hugh Saddler founded the company ''Energy Strategies'' in 1982 and is its Managing Director.
