Geologically, the [[Caspian Sea]], like the [[Black Sea|Black]] and [[Mediterranean Sea|Mediterranean]] seas, is a remnant of the ancient [[Tethys Ocean]]. The deepest area is oceanic rather than continental crust. However, it is generally regarded by geographers as a large [[endorheic]] [[salt lake]].

